        <tr id="comment-body-16461"><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
            <p>I don’t think the actual UI code gets us very far, but I do think having the design mock artifacts is fantastic! Probably after this current push we should see if we can integrate IBM’s Figma for Carbon kit with our Figma setup… That’s more likely to get us to an easily usable artifact.</p>
        </td></tr>
                <tr id="comment-header-16761"><td bgcolor="#f0f0f0">
            Comment by  
                                                    
                
        
            <a class="user-hover" rel="557058:c0b40bdd-71df-4365-93ef-efc2b70107da"
                id="word_commented_557058:c0b40bdd-71df-4365-93ef-efc2b70107da"
                href="https://uwdigi.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=557058%3Ac0b40bdd-71df-4365-93ef-efc2b70107da">
                    Male Samuel
                </a>

                                        <font size="-2">
            [
                <font color="#336699">13/Nov/25</font>

                            ]
            </font>

        </td></tr>
        <tr id="comment-body-16761"><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
            <p>A few questions regarding the overall scope of work for this feature:</p>

<ol>
	<li><b>Analyzer Coverage:</b><br/>
Is this feature intended to work exclusively with ASTM-enabled analyzers, or should we design it to support other communication protocols as well (e.g., HL7, CSV imports, or direct OpenELIS data entry)?</li>
	<li><b>Analyzer Configuration UI:</b><br/>
Do we already have a <a href="https://uwdigi.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/OG/pages/640319495/OpenELIS+Global+Software+Release+Roadmap#%F0%9F%94%AC-Analyzer-Integration-%26-Management" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">UI for configuring or mapping ASTM-enabled analyzers</a>, or would part of this work involve creating a configuration panel for instrument setup and QC data mapping?</li>
	<li><b>Backend Components:</b><br/>
While I see that we already have <a href="https://github.com/DIGI-UW/openelisglobal-plugins/tree/develop" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">plugins</a> for instrument communication, do we currently have backend components for:
	<ul>
		<li>A Westgard rule evaluation service or basic rule engine</li>
		<li>QC-related database models</li>
		<li>An alerting or notification service for rule violations<br/>
Or should these be developed as part of this story’s implementation?</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li><b>Rule Definition and Management:</b><br/>
How do we plan to define and maintain the Westgard rules?<br/>
Should rules be configurable through a UI (for admins to add or modify), or are we expecting them to be defined via configuration files?</li>
	<li><b>Data Flow:</b><br/>
Are QC results expected to be synchronized in real time from analyzers, or will there be scheduled batch imports?</li>
</ol>

        </td></tr>
                <tr id="comment-header-16762"><td bgcolor="#f0f0f0">
