        <tr id="comment-body-16763"><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
            <p><a href="https://uwdigi.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=557058%3Ac0b40bdd-71df-4365-93ef-efc2b70107da" class="user-hover" rel="557058:c0b40bdd-71df-4365-93ef-efc2b70107da" data-account-id="557058:c0b40bdd-71df-4365-93ef-efc2b70107da" accountid="557058:c0b40bdd-71df-4365-93ef-efc2b70107da" rel="noreferrer">Male Samuel</a> I’ve added some more details above, which detail out the rules for the rule builder, we do indeed already have a mechanism to connect to the analyzers to OpenELIS, and there is a different story to enable the mapping. This would be to build out the rules to run the checks against the QC data, and then show the alerts, and log corrective actions. </p>


